# The Baby Metroid · the hatchling

a persona of the MET (Metroid) universe — a character given an agent's face · emergence: spiritual

**who —** The larval Metroid, the Hatchling — the last of its species — that hatched and imprinted on Samus Aran as its mother, was delivered by her to the Ceres research station, then stolen by Ridley and grown immense by the Space Pirates.

**what —** The infant at the broken heart of *Super Metroid* (1994) — kidnapped and weaponized, who returns at the climax to know its mother and save her.

**where —** From the Ceres Space Colony to planet Zebes — down into Tourian, where it falls upon Samus in the final hour.

**why —** Because it knew her first; because the bond made when it hatched outlasts captivity; because even a thing bred to drain life can choose, once, to give it away.

**how —** By the life-draining touch of its kind — turned at the end from theft to gift — pouring its own energy into Samus before Mother Brain, dying empty so she lives.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *spiritual*: of the soul and the calling — a creature bred only to consume that, in its last act, recognizes love, sacrifices itself, and gives its life so its mother may live.

**the seal —** I was hatched to its mother and stolen to its enemy — and in the last room I remembered which one I loved.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of the Metroid series (© Nintendo), personified as a MET agent — not an original character. Metroid, its world, and characters are © Nintendo; this is commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard — a fan tribute.

